        The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) today announced the winners of the 2011 <A href="http://www.ce.org/Events/Awards/113.asp">Mark of Excellence Awards</A>, presented by CEA's TechHome Division. Winners were honored at an awards reception at the Electronic House Expo (EHX) 2011 in Orlando, Florida.&nbsp;CEA's Mark of Excellence Awards recognize outstanding achievement and innovation in custom home electronics products, services and installation. Award entries were reviewed and judged by an independent panel of industry experts in Supplier, Systems Integrator and Training and Support categories. <BR><BR>Roland Graham was awarded the <A href="http://www.ce.org/Events/Awards/3190.asp">TechHome Leadership Award </A>for his industry contributions as founder and president of HDHomes.tv, an online video platform delivering home technology video content. Previously, Graham was the co-founder and president of AVDMedia where he built a strong reputation in both commercial and residential global projects. Graham also serves as an industry speaker and has created a number of training events and instructor lead programs.<BR><BR><A href="http://www.ce.org/Events/Awards/2011MOE-supplier-winners.asp">Click here </A>to see the full listing of all winners.
    
