    <div class="article-content">
        <div class="sub-content-header">Microsoft Keynote and Major Product Announcements Kick Off 2011 CES</div>
        <span class="smallText">Jan 07, 2011 11:57:38</span>
        
        <P>A preshow address from Microsoft's Steve Ballmer and innovative product announcements from major technology companies fueled excitement on the eve of the 2011 International CES, the world's largest tradeshow for consumer technology. <BR><BR>Owned and produced by the <A href="http://www.CE.org" target=_blank>Consumer Electronics Association (CEA), </A>the 2011 International CES opened runs through Sunday, January 9. <BR><BR>"The innovative products announced in our pre-CES events have created tremendous buzz as we kick off the world's largest innovation event – the 2011 International CES," said Gary Shapiro, president and CEO, CEA. "The 2011 CES will be a phenomenal show across all measures with <A href="http://www.CESweb.org/CESexhibitors">2,700 exhibitors</A> launching some 20,000 new technology products. There will be more innovation unveiled this week at CES than the rest of the year combined." <BR><BR>In other pre-show news, CEA released its Global CE Sales and Forecast. According to new data from CEA, consumer electronics sales worldwide in 2011 will generate $964 billion in retail revenue. <BR><BR>On Tuesday evening, January 4th, the seventh annual CES Unveiled: The Official Press Event of the International CES kicked off the pre-CES media events at The Venetian. The event hosted a record number of more than 1,500 media. With 66 exhibitors, including Cobra, Dolby, Lenovo, OnStar and Samsung, CES Unveiled featured the latest technology innovations including tablets, health and fitness products, accessories and eco-friendly devices. <BR><BR>Product announcements continued on Wednesday with CES Press Day, featuring 14 exhibitor press conferences. CES exhibitors making new product announcements included LG, which announced a Smart TV platform for content sharing and downloading apps; Intel, which introduced its second generation Intel Core processor, 'Sandy Bridge;' and Motorola, which announced the Xoom tablet, the first Android Honeycomb tablet with webcam, HD video and HD widescreen display. <BR><BR>During his pre-CES keynote address on Wednesday evening, Microsoft Corp. President and CEO Steve Ballmer announced that 8 million XBOX 360 Kinect devices were sold in the first 60 days, shattering the company's estimate of 5 million.&nbsp; <BR><BR>"It's been the biggest holiday and year ever for XBOX," Ballmer said in the Microsoft keynote at International CES.&nbsp; <BR><BR>Microsoft also previewed how consumers will be able to use their XBOX 360 to view Netflix and Hulu Plus content this spring by using Kinect as the remote control. The next version of Windows, meanwhile, will support System on a Chip to help create new types of hardware. <BR><BR>"Whatever device you use now or in the future, Windows will be there," Ballmer concluded.</P>
    
